getNames

public Set<String> getNames()
Access a list of database names that preside under the blast database root directory. This method will return the base names of the databases (i.e. 'nr.01.pin', 'nr.01.psi' will be flattened to 'nr').

getFiles

public Collection<File> getFiles(String key)
Access all files for a specified database name. For example providing "uniprot_sprot" will return "uniprot_sprot.psi", "uniprot_sprot.pin" and the other database files.

Parameters:
key - database name or alias
Returns:
all files for the given database name

getPath

public File getPath(String key)
Returns the path to the named database. The raw name is first search and then aliases. If not database is found then an InvalidParameterException is thrown.

Parameters:
key - name or alias (e.g. nr or Non-redundant)
Returns:
full path (i.e. getRoot() + name) which can be used as the database argument when creating a blast search
